  "text": "Blood specimens were cultured for >8 weeks as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Bartonella culture-positive specimens were confirmed to be Bartontella species by using microbiological observations and molecular assays. Nucleic acids were isolated from culture-positive blood samples and subjected to PCR amplification of a 338-bp fragment of the gltA gene. The PCR product was sequenced by using the Sanger method.",
